# Provider Abstraction

- Keep provider-specific details behind a provider trait.
- Normalize provider responses into internal response types.
- Keep the mock provider working without network access or API keys.
- Make mock latency, failure rate, token estimates, and pricing configurable.
- Keep provider selection separate from HTTP route handlers.
- Keep fallback logic unit-testable.
- Avoid vendor lock-in in core abstractions.
- Never log provider secrets.
- Use request timeouts for outbound calls once real providers are added.
- The provider trait should conceptually support `name()`, supported models, `chat_completion(request)`, and optional health/status later.
